RP 0003 1stPass [discover and navigation]: Result card summary overlay fails to pop up when triggered.
Tester: Marylle Laguna

[Summary]
When a user clicks on a search result card, the application fails to execute the target node routing. The application remains entirely static, and no navigation or action occurs upon the click event.

[Precondition]
  - User has executed a search query.
  - Search results are populated and visible on the page.
 Software version: RP.010.004
 Software configuration: Internal QA Environment
 Hardware specification: Windows 11 Desktop
 Network configuration: Wi-Fi

[Steps to reproduce]
  1. Navigate to the main search of Rotten potato 
  2. Input any search query and hit enter to load the search results.
  3. Click directly on one of the populated search result cards.

[Actual results]
  1. Nothing happens. The UI remains completely static, there is no redirection to the target node, and no visual feedback/error is presented

[Expected results]
  1. The user should be immediately routed and redirected to the specific details page/target node corresponding to the clicked search card.

[Additional information]
 A screenshot showing the successful redirection with the flawed credentials

[Is this Breakage?]
  No, missed from previous pass
 
[Previous code tested]
  N/A
 
